# Configureation
To configure the servers the frontend needs VITE_BACKEND_URL set in the .env
the backend needs FRONTEND_URL and JWT_SECRET set in the .env

Deployment over railway uses the start script
```
npm install
npm run build
npx serve -s dist
```
for the frontend and
```
npm install
node index.js {port}
```
for the backend

# Notes:
The backend and frontend can run on the same machine for simplicity.
Railway automatically provides URLs; ensure VITE_BACKEND_URL points to the backendâ€™s public URL.
The backend listens on the specified port; the frontend communicates via VITE_BACKEND_URL.

